---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import ChatInterface from '../components/ChatInterface.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Ask the site — Jody Brewster"
  description="A chat interface over Jody Brewster's published essays, notes, and case briefs. Speaks in third person, cites its sources, refuses what isn't in the corpus."
>
  <main class="page active" style="padding: 56px 0 100px;">
    <div class="chat-shell">
      <div class="preamble">
        <h1>Ask the site.</h1>
        <p>This is a chat interface on the personal site of someone who has written essays arguing that <a href="/notes/chat-is-not-the-answer">chat is a bad UI for AI</a>. The contradiction is the point.</p>
        <p>It's here because the alternative — pretending the question doesn't come up — felt worse. So: this is the most opinionated chat I could build. It speaks <em>about</em> Jody in the third person, not <em>as</em> him. It cites its sources. It refuses some questions on purpose.</p>

        <div class="honesty-card">
          <p class="h"><svg class="icon sm"><use href="#i-shield"/></svg> What this is, and isn't</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Reads from</strong> Jody's published essays, notes, and anonymized case briefs on this site.</li>
            <li><strong>Speaks in third person.</strong> "Jody has written…" not "I have written…" — voice cloning is a design choice not worth making.</li>
            <li><strong>Refuses</strong> questions about specific clients, projects, employers, or anything that would impersonate his opinions on something he hasn't written about.</li>
            <li><strong>Will be wrong sometimes.</strong> Use the cited essays as the source of truth, not the synthesis above them.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ChatInterface />
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
